com.carteryagemann.AICS

Class IntentHeader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.carteryagemann.AICS.IntentHeader
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActivityIntentHeader, BroadcastIntentHeader, ServiceIntentHeader

    public abstract class IntentHeader
extends java.lang.Object
    A header contains important information about an Android intent which isn't contained in the intent itself. This includes information such as the sender and receiver of the intent.

    • Method Detail

      • parseIntentType

        public static short parseIntentType(java.nio.ByteBuffer buffer)
                             throws java.text.ParseException,
                                    java.nio.BufferUnderflowException
        Returns the type of the first intent header in the buffer. The returned value can then be used to determine which constructor should be called on the buffer.
        Parameters:
        buffer - The buffer to parse. The header must start at the current position of this buffer.
        Returns:
        The type of the intent header at the start of the buffer.
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - If type can't be determined
        java.nio.BufferUnderflowException - If buffer is too tiny to be an intent header.

      • parseIntentType

        public static short parseIntentType(byte[] array)
                             throws java.text.ParseException,
                                    java.nio.BufferUnderflowException
        Returns the type of the first intent header in the buffer. The returned value can then be used to determine which constructor should be called on the buffer.
        Parameters:
        array - The byte array to parse. The header must start at the beginning of this array.
        Returns:
        The type of the intent header at the start of the buffer.
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - If type can't be determined.
        java.nio.BufferUnderflowException - If buffer is too tiny to be an intent header.

      • toByteBuffer

        protected abstract java.nio.ByteBuffer toByteBuffer()
        Convert the contents of the intent header into a ByteBuffer which is ready to be written to a file. This buffer only contains the header. To flatten the data, use getIntentData().toByteBuffer().
        Returns:
        A ByteBuffer containing the contents of the intent header.

      • getSize

        public abstract int getSize()
        Calculates the total number of bytes needed to write this header.
        Returns:
        The number of bytes this header will use when flattened into a sequence of bytes.
